---

# 🚨 Error

```text
required a bean of type 'RedisTemplate' that could not be found
```

👉 Translation:

> You defined `RedisAuthTransactionService` expecting a `RedisTemplate`,
> but Spring **doesn’t have one registered**.

---

# 🧠 Why this happened

You probably:

* removed old Redis config ❌
* or changed template type to `RedisTemplate<String, AuthTransaction>` ❌
* but didn’t define a bean for it

---

# ✅ FIX (you MUST add Redis config bean)

Create a config class:

## ✅ `RedisConfig.java`

```java
@Configuration
public class RedisConfig {

    @Bean
    public RedisTemplate<String, Object> redisTemplate(RedisConnectionFactory connectionFactory) {
        RedisTemplate<String, Object> template = new RedisTemplate<>();
        template.setConnectionFactory(connectionFactory);

        // Key serializer
        template.setKeySerializer(new StringRedisSerializer());
        template.setHashKeySerializer(new StringRedisSerializer());

        // Value serializer (IMPORTANT)
        GenericJackson2JsonRedisSerializer serializer =
                new GenericJackson2JsonRedisSerializer();

        template.setValueSerializer(serializer);
        template.setHashValueSerializer(serializer);

        template.afterPropertiesSet();
        return template;
    }
}
```

---

# ✅ Then update your service

Make sure your service uses the same type:

```java
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Service
public class RedisAuthTransactionService {

    private static final String PREFIX = "auth:state:";

    private final RedisTemplate<String, Object> redisTemplate;

    public void save(AuthTransaction tx) {
        redisTemplate.opsForValue().set(PREFIX + tx.getState(), tx, Duration.ofMinutes(5));
    }

    public AuthTransaction findByState(String state) {
        Object value = redisTemplate.opsForValue().get(PREFIX + state);
        return value == null ? null : (AuthTransaction) value;
    }

    public void delete(String state) {
        redisTemplate.delete(PREFIX + state);
    }
}
```

